name: Mould Dimensions are within Shop Drawings Tolerance
Detailed inspection of Mould and cage
All Stainless Steel Ferrules are installed in accordance with Drawings

All Blockout Conduits are installed in accordance with Drawings
All Lifting Inserts are installed in accordance with Drawings
All Bartek Couplers are installed in accordance with Drawings
All LENTON Couplers are installed in accordance with Drawings and staggered with KSN16M in web
All Bearing plates in Diaphragms are installed as per drawings

100mm long 6mm fillet welds between bars/ 55mm long butt welds
Coil Number Used for this Cast
Stressing Records subject to Client Review
HOLD POINT FOR CLIENT TO SIGN OFF
All Temperature Loggers are installed as per Approved WMS
Ensure All temperature Loggers are Working (Check Maturix)

All Sliding arms are locked in position
All accrow props are locked in position
Dimensions of Tub and Webb are correct
All feet for tubs resting on mould & bolted down
Slump within Allowable Tolerance (180+/-40) (Tested 1st truck and subsequently for every 20m3)

Verify Destressing/Transfer of stress required strength
Specify Strength at time of destressing
Specify strength at time of lifting
Mould and Steam Cured until the curing strength achieved
Lifted and Handled as per Drawings
Storage as per Approved Temporary Works Drawings

Cast-in Items are all in Place and within Specified Tolerance
Strands are Cut Flush and Epoxied except debonding strands
Water Removed out of Cooling Pipes

Third Reading (At 28 days after stage 1 casting)
Final Reading (7 days prior to scheduled delivery)
